Package: tigers
Version: 0.1
Date: 2023-10-05
Title: Tools for Integrating Geography, Environment, and Remote Sensing
Authors@R: c(person("Emmanuel", "Paradis", role = c("aut", "cre", "cph"), email = "Emmanuel.Paradis@ird.fr", comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0003-3092-2199")))
Imports: stats
ZipData: no
Description: Functions for handling and manipulating polygons, coordinates, and other geographical objects. The tools include: polygon areas, barycentric and trilinear coordinates, convex hull for polygons, triangulation of polygons, great circle and geodesic distances, Hausdorff distance, and reduced major axis.
License: GPL-3
URL: https://github.com/emmanuelparadis/tigers
BugReports: https://github.com/emmanuelparadis/tigers/issues
